Name: import-env-file
Version: 2020.12.3
Summary: import .env file environment variables into python
Home-page: https://github.com/andrewp-as-is/import-env-file.py
License: Unlicense
Description: <!--
        https://readme42.com
        -->
        
        
        [![](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/import-env-file.svg?maxAge=3600)](https://pypi.org/project/import-env-file/)
        [![](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-Unlicense-blue.svg?longCache=True)](https://unlicense.org/)
        
        ### Installation
        ```bash
        $ [sudo] pip install import-env-file
        ```
        
        #### Examples
        `.env`
        ```python
        DB_NAME="name"
        ...
        ```
        
        `settings.py`
        ```python
        import import_env_file
        import os
        
        DATABASES = {
            'default': {
                'NAME': os.getenv('DB_NAME'),
            }
        }
        ```
        
